1
00:00:01,174 --> 00:00:02,640
[♪]

2
00:01:04,707 --> 00:01:06,440
YUKO:
Honestly, doctor,

3
00:01:06,474 --> 00:01:09,174
if we left it to you,
you'd never take a vacation.

4
00:01:09,207 --> 00:01:10,974
Now I want you to spend
this weekend just relaxing,

5
00:01:11,007 --> 00:01:11,974
all right?

6
00:01:12,007 --> 00:01:13,207
You'll love this resort.

7
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:14,307
O'SHAY:
Yeah, B-but...

8
00:01:14,340 --> 00:01:15,674
YUKO:
I've got you scheduled

9
00:01:15,707 --> 00:01:17,674
for golf at 6,
yoga at 10,

10
00:01:17,707 --> 00:01:19,407
then hiking, tennis,
bowling, water aerobics--

11
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:21,040
O'SHAY:
Very relaxing.

12
00:01:21,074 --> 00:01:23,207
I should be in a coma by dinner.

13
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:25,307
I'll pick you both up Monday.

14
00:01:25,340 --> 00:01:27,907
Astro, you watch
over the doctor.
Right.

15
00:01:27,940 --> 00:01:30,540
Look, everyone.
There's the town of Bella Notte.

16
00:01:36,007 --> 00:01:37,907
Wow. Wonder what
that tent's for.

17
00:01:45,274 --> 00:01:46,307
Dr. O'Shay!

18
00:01:47,540 --> 00:01:49,007
Welcome to Bella Notte.

19
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:50,340
I'm Mayor Craven.

20
00:01:50,374 --> 00:01:52,340
It's an honor to have
such a famous scientist

21
00:01:52,374 --> 00:01:53,574
in our fair city.

22
00:01:53,607 --> 00:01:57,140
O'SHAY:
Uh, thank you.

23
00:01:57,174 --> 00:01:59,274
CRAVEN:
Now, I've arranged
a few activities for your visit:

24
00:01:59,307 --> 00:02:00,474
Pickle judging, thumb wrestling

25
00:02:00,507 --> 00:02:02,574
and a tour
of the kibble factory.

26
00:02:02,607 --> 00:02:04,307
Doctor, look.

27
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:06,574
A robot circus
is coming into town.

28
00:02:06,607 --> 00:02:09,340
Uh, did you say
a robot circus?

29
00:02:09,374 --> 00:02:10,407
Oh, my, yes.

30
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:13,140
Definitely a must-see.

31
00:02:13,174 --> 00:02:16,374
A traveling circus
composed entirely of robots.

32
00:02:16,407 --> 00:02:18,474
They're really quite famous in
these parts. And I must say,

33
00:02:18,507 --> 00:02:20,907
you haven't lived till you've--
GUSTAV: Hey, Craven.

34
00:02:20,940 --> 00:02:23,407
Since when do you allow robots
to put up posters

35
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:24,907
for their so-called circus?

36
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:27,040
Uh, Mr. Gustav, I, uh...

37
00:02:27,074 --> 00:02:28,940
Get in.

38
00:02:28,974 --> 00:02:30,440
Yes, sir.

39
00:02:30,474 --> 00:02:32,407
Uh, well,
if you'll excuse me.

40
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:33,440
GUSTAV:
Get in!

41
00:02:33,474 --> 00:02:35,574
It looks like some robots

42
00:02:35,607 --> 00:02:37,974
are starting to think they're
just like human beings.

43
00:02:39,174 --> 00:02:40,874
I don't like it.

44
00:02:48,074 --> 00:02:49,940
Friendly little town.

45
00:02:49,974 --> 00:02:51,274
That's Mr. Gustav,

46
00:02:51,307 --> 00:02:53,940
owner of Jade Refinery,
and the richest man in town.

47
00:02:53,974 --> 00:02:54,874
He pretty much
runs this city.

48
00:02:59,307 --> 00:03:02,074
All right. Let's just
go over this

49
00:03:02,107 --> 00:03:04,374
one more time,
shall we, Mr. Mayor?

50
00:03:04,407 --> 00:03:06,307
I don't like robots

51
00:03:06,340 --> 00:03:08,940
and I don't want them
doing business in my city.

52
00:03:08,974 --> 00:03:09,974
Robots need to know
their place.

53
00:03:10,007 --> 00:03:12,040
They're servants
and nothing more.

54
00:03:12,074 --> 00:03:14,074
That's the way
it's always been,

55
00:03:14,107 --> 00:03:16,374
and that's the way
it's gonna stay. Got it?

56
00:03:16,407 --> 00:03:17,607
Yes, sir.

57
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:21,440
Anyway, I've got plans
for that circus.

58
00:03:21,474 --> 00:03:22,574
ANNOUNCER:
Ladies and gentlemen,

59
00:03:22,607 --> 00:03:24,007
boys and girls,

60
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:26,474
children of all ages...

61
00:03:26,507 --> 00:03:28,007
welcome to the
super-sensational,

62
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,074
ultra-gyrational,

63
00:03:29,107 --> 00:03:31,440
quite educational Robot Circus.

64
00:03:31,474 --> 00:03:33,040
Let the show begin.

65
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,440
Yahoo!

66
00:03:43,507 --> 00:03:44,307
Yeah!
Yeah!

67
00:03:45,940 --> 00:03:46,940
BOTH:
Ta-daa!

68
00:03:46,974 --> 00:03:49,140
[CHEERING]

69
00:03:53,707 --> 00:03:55,674
ASTRO:
<i>It's Mr. Gustav.</i>

70
00:03:55,707 --> 00:03:58,507
<i>But why is he here?</i>
<i>I thought he hated robots.</i>

71
00:03:58,540 --> 00:04:00,540
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

72
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,407
Look out!

73
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,274
[CROWD SCREAMING]

74
00:04:16,607 --> 00:04:17,907
ANNOUNCER:
Ladies and gentlemen,

75
00:04:17,940 --> 00:04:20,874
please remain calm!
Don't panic!

76
00:04:25,738 --> 00:04:26,971
[CROWD SCREAMING]

77
00:04:27,005 --> 00:04:28,805
Please!
Stay calm, folks!

78
00:04:32,571 --> 00:04:33,338
Cookie!

79
00:04:34,671 --> 00:04:35,538
Whoa!

80
00:04:37,038 --> 00:04:38,838
Bon-Bon,
throw me up there!

81
00:04:38,871 --> 00:04:40,238
You bet.

82
00:04:40,571 --> 00:04:41,671
Yee-haw!

83
00:04:43,505 --> 00:04:45,238
Reno, be careful.

84
00:04:45,271 --> 00:04:46,671
I'll be fine.

85
00:04:46,705 --> 00:04:47,471
Oh. Oh! Whoa!

86
00:04:52,838 --> 00:04:54,638
Huh?

87
00:04:54,671 --> 00:04:55,971
[COOKIE YELLING]

88
00:04:56,805 --> 00:04:57,805
Oh!

89
00:04:58,705 --> 00:04:59,471
Ha-ha-ha.

90
00:05:01,371 --> 00:05:02,305
You okay,
Cookie?

91
00:05:03,938 --> 00:05:05,305
Safe.
Thanks.

92
00:05:08,605 --> 00:05:09,771
O'SHAY:
Astro.

93
00:05:09,805 --> 00:05:11,805
Are you hurt?

94
00:05:11,838 --> 00:05:14,571
Doctor, that boy robot
is a human.

95
00:05:14,605 --> 00:05:16,705
Wh-what?

96
00:05:16,738 --> 00:05:18,438
What a terrible accident.

97
00:05:18,471 --> 00:05:19,938
But we're all fine,
thanks to Astro.

98
00:05:19,971 --> 00:05:22,871
That was no accident.

99
00:05:22,905 --> 00:05:26,938
Astro says he saw the rope being
cut by one of Gustav's men. Oh?

100
00:05:26,971 --> 00:05:28,571
RENO:
There you go.
All fixed up.

101
00:05:30,005 --> 00:05:31,005
Now, let's see you move it.

102
00:05:31,038 --> 00:05:32,538
Perfect.

103
00:05:32,571 --> 00:05:33,571
Good as new.

104
00:05:33,605 --> 00:05:34,371
Great job, Reno.

105
00:05:36,305 --> 00:05:38,538
Reno, you've
repaired him already?

106
00:05:38,571 --> 00:05:39,538
Sure.

107
00:05:42,005 --> 00:05:45,271
Using just this
flexation sensor?

108
00:05:45,305 --> 00:05:47,371
Yeah.
I use whatever works.

109
00:05:47,405 --> 00:05:49,571
You know,
Reno made that gadget.

110
00:05:49,605 --> 00:05:52,605
He's smarter than a barrel
full of, eh, smart things.

111
00:05:52,638 --> 00:05:54,705
I agree.

112
00:05:54,738 --> 00:05:57,971
Uh, Reno, I can see you have
an amazing talent for robotics.

113
00:05:58,005 --> 00:06:00,238
He's a veritable
virtuoso.

114
00:06:00,271 --> 00:06:01,671
He could be
a scientist.

115
00:06:01,705 --> 00:06:04,371
Why, if he had the
proper education, he--

116
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:06,005
Aw, come on.
It's no big deal.

117
00:06:06,038 --> 00:06:08,705
I think it's perfectly natural

118
00:06:08,738 --> 00:06:10,838
for a robot to know
about robotics and stuff.

119
00:06:10,871 --> 00:06:12,338
ASTRO:
Reno...

120
00:06:12,371 --> 00:06:15,205
why are you pretending
to be a robot?

121
00:06:15,671 --> 00:06:17,271
[SCREAMING]

122
00:06:19,638 --> 00:06:21,571
I mean,
you're human.

123
00:06:21,605 --> 00:06:25,005
What are you talking about?
I'm a robot.

124
00:06:25,038 --> 00:06:27,305
You must have
a short circuit somewhere.

125
00:06:27,338 --> 00:06:29,338
That's right.
He's a robot.

126
00:06:29,371 --> 00:06:31,971
You're talking crazy.
Now get out of here.

127
00:06:32,005 --> 00:06:34,271
Yeah.
Beat it!

128
00:06:34,305 --> 00:06:36,871
Go away!
Stop it!
All of you!

129
00:06:36,905 --> 00:06:39,538
What has gotten
into you?

130
00:06:39,571 --> 00:06:42,571
Remember, these people
saved our circus. And us.

131
00:06:42,605 --> 00:06:44,538
I apologize for my
overzealous friends.

132
00:06:44,571 --> 00:06:47,538
We are all still
a bit shaken.

133
00:06:47,571 --> 00:06:49,571
Now, if you'll excuse us,
we've got work to do.

134
00:06:55,305 --> 00:06:56,371
Reno.

135
00:06:56,805 --> 00:06:59,538
Reno, is it you?

136
00:06:59,571 --> 00:07:00,671
Uh, huh?

137
00:07:00,705 --> 00:07:03,805
You look different,
but I think--

138
00:07:03,838 --> 00:07:06,971
Well, I mean, if it is you,
I'm sorry about before.

139
00:07:07,005 --> 00:07:09,538
I didn't mean
to cause trouble.

140
00:07:18,638 --> 00:07:19,671
Guess I'm busted, huh?

141
00:07:19,705 --> 00:07:21,238
Mm-hm.

142
00:07:21,271 --> 00:07:24,638
You see, I was abandoned
when I was a baby.

143
00:07:24,671 --> 00:07:28,371
The folks in the circus, uh,
found me and took me in.

144
00:07:28,405 --> 00:07:30,438
You mean, you were
raised by robots?

145
00:07:30,471 --> 00:07:32,771
Sure. I've been
really lucky.

146
00:07:32,805 --> 00:07:34,571
Since I was
a little kid,

147
00:07:34,605 --> 00:07:36,871
I've had, like,
five fathers and one mom.

148
00:07:36,905 --> 00:07:39,571
Of course, I go broke
every Father's Day,

149
00:07:39,605 --> 00:07:41,405
but they're worth it.
Yeah, I can see they are.

150
00:07:45,005 --> 00:07:46,738
You see that circus tent?

151
00:07:46,771 --> 00:07:48,405
That's my home,
no matter where it is.

152
00:07:48,438 --> 00:07:51,005
And those robots are my family.

153
00:07:51,038 --> 00:07:53,805
The best family
in the whole world.

154
00:07:54,738 --> 00:07:55,805
I owe them everything.

155
00:07:55,838 --> 00:07:57,538
But why the disguise?

156
00:07:57,571 --> 00:08:00,238
Because some folks might not
like the idea

157
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:01,605
of robots raising a human.

158
00:08:01,638 --> 00:08:04,438
I care for my family,
and I know they care for me,

159
00:08:04,471 --> 00:08:06,438
but if it ever got out
that I'm a human,

160
00:08:06,471 --> 00:08:09,705
well, face it,
I'm just still a kid.

161
00:08:09,738 --> 00:08:12,305
I could be
taken away from them.

162
00:08:12,338 --> 00:08:13,571
That's why
it's gotta be a secret.

163
00:08:13,605 --> 00:08:15,238
Too bad.
Well, then,

164
00:08:15,271 --> 00:08:17,238
we'll just have to make sure

165
00:08:17,271 --> 00:08:19,205
it stays a secret, won't we?

166
00:08:20,805 --> 00:08:22,505
You bet, Astro. Thanks.

167
00:08:29,638 --> 00:08:30,871
[GUSTAV GRUNTS]

168
00:08:30,905 --> 00:08:34,405
I want that robot circus
crushed. Do you hear me?

169
00:08:34,438 --> 00:08:36,938
Snoop around. Dig up
all the dirt you can.

170
00:08:36,971 --> 00:08:39,571
Get me something
I can use against them!

171
00:08:39,605 --> 00:08:41,571
Now, get going!

172
00:08:41,605 --> 00:08:44,271
Mercy. We're in deep doughnuts.

173
00:08:49,405 --> 00:08:51,638
BON-BON:
Mamma llama! Are you sure?

174
00:08:51,671 --> 00:08:52,971
It's only
a matter of time

175
00:08:53,005 --> 00:08:55,571
before Gustav
figures out our secret.

176
00:08:55,605 --> 00:08:58,238
Boss, we've gotta get
out of here now.

177
00:08:58,271 --> 00:09:01,271
If we stick around, we're
headed for big time trouble.

178
00:09:06,605 --> 00:09:09,771
The boy is talented.
He should be in school. Pity.

179
00:09:09,805 --> 00:09:11,305
Ahem.

180
00:09:11,338 --> 00:09:12,838
Ah, Mr. Panna Cotta.

181
00:09:12,871 --> 00:09:15,705
Doctor,
I have a favor to ask.

182
00:09:15,738 --> 00:09:19,005
Craven...call out the police!

183
00:09:19,038 --> 00:09:21,571
I want those circus
robots arrested.

184
00:09:21,605 --> 00:09:23,971
B-b-but why?

185
00:09:24,005 --> 00:09:26,838
They've been concealing
a human child.

186
00:09:26,871 --> 00:09:28,971
They've obviously
kidnapped the boy.

187
00:09:29,005 --> 00:09:32,771
As mayor, it's your duty
to see that justice is done!

188
00:09:32,805 --> 00:09:34,271
Boy? But I didn't--

189
00:09:34,305 --> 00:09:37,505
Of course not, you idiot.

190
00:09:37,538 --> 00:09:39,538
They've kept him
disguised as a robot.

191
00:09:39,571 --> 00:09:41,638
If you need proof, just
look at these photographs.

192
00:09:46,005 --> 00:09:47,505
So you want me to take

193
00:09:47,538 --> 00:09:49,838
this letter to Dr. O'Shay
at his hotel, right?

194
00:09:49,871 --> 00:09:53,938
Yes, Reno. And be sure you hand
it to him personally.

195
00:09:53,971 --> 00:09:55,238
You got it.

196
00:09:59,571 --> 00:10:00,571
BOTH:
Reno.

197
00:10:00,605 --> 00:10:01,938
Boss?

198
00:10:01,971 --> 00:10:04,705
This is it.
We're leaving town now.

199
00:10:04,738 --> 00:10:06,405
MARSHMALLOW: Right. Let's go.
BON-BON: Let's move it.

200
00:10:06,438 --> 00:10:08,405
[SIRENS WAILING]

201
00:10:12,871 --> 00:10:15,005
I'm sorry, Reno.

202
00:10:15,038 --> 00:10:16,705
Dr. O'Shay said
he had to

203
00:10:16,738 --> 00:10:18,805
run out
to do something.

204
00:10:18,838 --> 00:10:21,538
Okay. I'll wait till
he gets back.

205
00:10:21,571 --> 00:10:22,638
Huh?
Huh?

206
00:10:24,805 --> 00:10:27,571
They look like they're headed
toward the circus.

207
00:10:27,605 --> 00:10:29,271
Aw, we've been
found out.

208
00:10:31,638 --> 00:10:32,438
Hey! Huh?
Oh!

209
00:10:32,471 --> 00:10:35,205
Aw, there he is,
the poor little guy.

210
00:10:36,905 --> 00:10:38,805
The innocent victim
of this terrible crime.

211
00:10:38,838 --> 00:10:41,605
Get off.
So sad.

212
00:10:43,005 --> 00:10:45,738
Forced into a life
of treachery and deceit

213
00:10:45,771 --> 00:10:48,738
after that ruthless gang
of circus robots kidnapped him.

214
00:10:48,771 --> 00:10:50,771
Huh?
Ehh!

215
00:10:50,805 --> 00:10:52,371
Where are they?

216
00:10:52,405 --> 00:10:53,671
If they're caught,
will they be destroyed?

217
00:10:54,738 --> 00:10:55,938
Reno, don't do it.

218
00:10:55,971 --> 00:10:57,605
You will only
make things worse.

219
00:10:57,638 --> 00:10:58,971
Fear not, my friends.

220
00:10:59,005 --> 00:11:01,371
The robots will be
found and dismantled.

221
00:11:01,405 --> 00:11:02,938
And this child
will be sent

222
00:11:02,971 --> 00:11:04,771
to an orphanage
where he belongs.

223
00:11:04,805 --> 00:11:05,938
Right, Mr. Mayor?

224
00:11:05,971 --> 00:11:08,505
Y-yes.
It's just, well--

225
00:11:08,538 --> 00:11:09,971
No!

226
00:11:10,005 --> 00:11:11,305
It's the law!

227
00:11:11,338 --> 00:11:12,705
Take the boy
into custody now.

228
00:11:12,738 --> 00:11:15,938
Let him go.
I'm Reno's guardian.

229
00:11:15,971 --> 00:11:17,705
Doctor!

230
00:11:17,738 --> 00:11:20,705
I have the necessary
paperwork with me right here.

231
00:11:20,738 --> 00:11:21,871
[GROWLS]

232
00:11:23,405 --> 00:11:25,738
Fine. You may have
the boy, doctor,

233
00:11:25,771 --> 00:11:27,271
but kidnapping
is a police matter.

234
00:11:27,305 --> 00:11:29,471
Those robots
are criminals,

235
00:11:29,505 --> 00:11:31,605
and they're headed
for the scrap heap.

236
00:11:31,638 --> 00:11:33,671
And there's not a thing
you can do about that.

237
00:11:33,705 --> 00:11:36,271
Doctor, I'm going to
help them.

238
00:11:36,305 --> 00:11:37,871
And just how?

239
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:39,871
Are you planning
to fight the police?

240
00:11:39,905 --> 00:11:42,371
RENO:
Hey, don't sweat it, Astro.

241
00:11:42,405 --> 00:11:44,938
They'll never catch
my family. Or me.

242
00:11:44,971 --> 00:11:47,538
Reno! Your family has gone.

243
00:11:47,571 --> 00:11:49,671
Huh?

244
00:11:49,705 --> 00:11:52,271
They have already
left town.

245
00:11:52,305 --> 00:11:54,571
The ringmaster asked me
to be your guardian.

246
00:11:54,605 --> 00:11:55,838
He wants you to come back

247
00:11:55,871 --> 00:11:57,738
to the city with me
to study robotics.

248
00:11:57,771 --> 00:11:59,771
I don't believe you.

249
00:11:59,805 --> 00:12:01,805
My family would never go
and leave me.

250
00:12:01,838 --> 00:12:05,005
The ringmaster gave you
a letter to deliver.

251
00:12:05,038 --> 00:12:06,938
It's addressed
to you.

252
00:12:08,805 --> 00:12:12,405
OFFICER:
They must still be close.
Keep searching.

253
00:12:12,438 --> 00:12:16,638
PANNA COTTA:
<i>Dear Reno, by the time you</i>
<i>read this, we'll be long gone.</i>

254
00:12:16,671 --> 00:12:18,871
<i>We're sorry it had to</i>
<i>end this way.</i>

255
00:12:18,905 --> 00:12:21,671
<i>But you must understand,</i>
<i>we have our own lives to live.</i>

256
00:12:21,705 --> 00:12:23,738
<i>And dragging a human around</i>

257
00:12:23,771 --> 00:12:27,605
<i>has frankly gotten to be</i>
<i>a burden for all of us.</i>

258
00:12:27,638 --> 00:12:29,371
<i>You'll be better off</i>
<i>with Dr. O'Shay.</i>

259
00:12:29,405 --> 00:12:32,238
<i>Please, don't try to find us.</i>

260
00:12:34,571 --> 00:12:35,605
[GRUNTS]

261
00:12:35,638 --> 00:12:37,538
It's because
they care.

262
00:12:37,571 --> 00:12:39,471
Huh?

263
00:12:39,505 --> 00:12:41,338
It's because they care for him
that they're doing this.

264
00:12:50,605 --> 00:12:51,638
[SIGHS]

265
00:12:54,838 --> 00:12:57,471
End of the line, folks.

266
00:12:57,505 --> 00:13:01,238
Good show.
At least Reno's safe.

267
00:13:01,271 --> 00:13:03,505
Right. We had to pretend
we didn't want him,

268
00:13:03,538 --> 00:13:05,705
or you know he'd have
tried to follow us.

269
00:13:05,738 --> 00:13:07,905
Yeah. I'll bet Reno

270
00:13:07,938 --> 00:13:11,538
will be a great
robotics engineer.

271
00:13:11,571 --> 00:13:14,405
Well, that's what
we all wanted for him.

272
00:13:14,438 --> 00:13:15,338
[YELLS]

273
00:13:16,838 --> 00:13:18,238
JELLY BEANS: Boss.

274
00:13:18,271 --> 00:13:19,371
Here they come.

275
00:13:19,405 --> 00:13:20,638
ASTRO:
Mr. Panna Cotta.

276
00:13:20,671 --> 00:13:21,971
Astro.

277
00:13:22,005 --> 00:13:25,405
We've got to hurry.
Here, grab hold.

278
00:13:25,438 --> 00:13:26,971
Does Dr. O'Shay
know about this?

279
00:13:27,005 --> 00:13:28,505
He will in a minute.

280
00:13:50,571 --> 00:13:52,238
[GASPS]

281
00:13:52,271 --> 00:13:54,271
I am so
not liking this.

282
00:13:54,305 --> 00:13:56,005
This way.

283
00:13:56,038 --> 00:13:57,271
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

284
00:13:59,805 --> 00:14:01,471
Wait.

285
00:14:01,505 --> 00:14:02,671
There they are.

286
00:14:02,705 --> 00:14:03,671
Over here.

287
00:14:03,705 --> 00:14:05,571
Okay. Hang on.

288
00:14:05,605 --> 00:14:06,671
MADELEINE:
Woo-hoo!

289
00:14:08,638 --> 00:14:09,838
[YELLING]

290
00:14:15,771 --> 00:14:16,671
CAPTAIN:
After him.

291
00:14:19,471 --> 00:14:20,871
Whoa! Ugh!

292
00:14:22,371 --> 00:14:23,571
Fire, fire, fire!

293
00:14:23,605 --> 00:14:25,371
[YELLING]

294
00:14:28,305 --> 00:14:29,605
ASTRO:
No!

295
00:14:29,638 --> 00:14:31,538
[YELLING]

296
00:14:39,621 --> 00:14:41,954
MAN:
What is it?
Why all the police?

297
00:14:41,988 --> 00:14:43,221
MAN 2:
They've got those
robot kidnappers cornered.

298
00:14:44,921 --> 00:14:47,821
Ha! Those tin troublemakers
will soon be history.

299
00:14:51,088 --> 00:14:53,588
Are you okay, Astro?

300
00:14:53,621 --> 00:14:56,321
Yeah, sure.
Unless you count great pain.

301
00:14:56,354 --> 00:14:58,421
Fine.

302
00:14:58,454 --> 00:15:03,854
Astro, we've decided to end this
in our own way.

303
00:15:03,888 --> 00:15:04,921
Huh?

304
00:15:04,954 --> 00:15:06,921
Hey, look.
They're coming out.

305
00:15:10,021 --> 00:15:11,321
CAPTAIN:
Hold your fire.

306
00:15:15,454 --> 00:15:17,988
What are they up to?

307
00:15:18,021 --> 00:15:21,054
Ladies and gentlemen,
boys and girls.

308
00:15:21,088 --> 00:15:22,921
Your attention, please.

309
00:15:26,188 --> 00:15:27,288
[GASPS]

310
00:15:30,521 --> 00:15:33,188
What are you waiting for?
Shoot them!

311
00:15:33,221 --> 00:15:35,888
But why, Mr. Gustav?
They're not trying to escape.

312
00:15:35,921 --> 00:15:38,221
[GROWLS]

313
00:15:38,254 --> 00:15:41,088
PANNA COTTA:
We proudly present
the Robot Circus

314
00:15:41,121 --> 00:15:42,488
in its farewell
performance.

315
00:15:42,521 --> 00:15:44,554
[GASPS]

316
00:15:44,588 --> 00:15:46,454
Astro.

317
00:15:46,488 --> 00:15:48,188
Your spotlight, sir.

318
00:15:53,988 --> 00:15:55,288
In the
center ring...

319
00:15:55,321 --> 00:15:57,954
the fairest flower
of the high wire...

320
00:15:57,988 --> 00:16:00,121
Mademoiselle
Madeleine.

321
00:16:05,354 --> 00:16:07,588
Ta-daa!

322
00:16:07,621 --> 00:16:09,921
Madeleine.

323
00:16:09,954 --> 00:16:13,588
MADELEINE:
<i>It was 11 years ago, Reno,</i>
<i>the day we first met you.</i>

324
00:16:13,621 --> 00:16:15,921
<i>The owner</i>
<i>of our circus retired,</i>

325
00:16:15,954 --> 00:16:18,488
<i>and we were all tossed</i>
<i>into the scrap heap.</i>

326
00:16:18,521 --> 00:16:20,088
BON-BON:
So, what are we
gonna do?

327
00:16:20,121 --> 00:16:22,921
No one wants to see us
perform anymore.

328
00:16:22,954 --> 00:16:25,321
I wish they'd just melt us down
and get it over with.

329
00:16:25,354 --> 00:16:26,454
[BABY SQUEALS]

330
00:16:26,488 --> 00:16:27,854
Huh?

331
00:16:27,888 --> 00:16:30,154
[CRYING]

332
00:16:31,854 --> 00:16:33,354
It's a baby.

333
00:16:33,388 --> 00:16:35,521
Hey. Don't cry.
Watch this.

334
00:16:35,554 --> 00:16:37,521
Myaah!

335
00:16:37,554 --> 00:16:39,821
Ahh!

336
00:16:39,854 --> 00:16:41,421
Look.
He likes it.

337
00:16:41,454 --> 00:16:44,254
Phew! He's gonna need
fresh diapers.

338
00:16:44,288 --> 00:16:46,454
And we'll have to
buy him more food.

339
00:16:46,488 --> 00:16:48,121
Buy?
With what?

340
00:16:50,321 --> 00:16:54,321
MADELEINE:
<i>And so we raised money</i>
<i>the only way we knew how.</i>

341
00:16:54,354 --> 00:16:58,821
<i>To us, Reno, you were hope.</i>
<i>A reason to go on.</i>

342
00:16:58,854 --> 00:17:01,088
COOKIE:
Thank you. Very kind.
Every bit helps.

343
00:17:01,121 --> 00:17:03,354
MADELEINE:
<i>A reason to revive</i>
<i>the Robot Circus.</i>

344
00:17:04,854 --> 00:17:06,454
Cookie.

345
00:17:06,488 --> 00:17:09,288
[CROWD APPLAUDING
AND CHEERING]

346
00:17:09,321 --> 00:17:11,121
Ooh, all right. Yeah.
Wonderful.

347
00:17:14,621 --> 00:17:16,354
RENO:
Bon-Bon.

348
00:17:16,388 --> 00:17:17,988
[GRUNTS]

349
00:17:18,021 --> 00:17:18,988
Woo-hoo-hoo!

350
00:17:22,988 --> 00:17:24,788
Jelly Beans.

351
00:17:26,888 --> 00:17:28,921
Ha-ha!

352
00:17:28,954 --> 00:17:30,521
Marshmallow.

353
00:17:37,121 --> 00:17:39,088
MARSHMALLOW:
<i>We've had good times,</i>
<i>right, Reno?</i>

354
00:17:39,121 --> 00:17:40,388
<i>Remember the fun summers?</i>

355
00:17:43,421 --> 00:17:44,421
[GRUNTING]

356
00:17:47,021 --> 00:17:48,954
[LAUGHS]

357
00:17:52,121 --> 00:17:54,321
MARSHMALLOW:
<i>And the cold winters?</i>

358
00:17:57,254 --> 00:17:59,221
It'll warm you up.

359
00:18:01,621 --> 00:18:03,421
RENO:
<i>You've been my parents...</i>

360
00:18:03,454 --> 00:18:05,421
<i>my teachers...</i>

361
00:18:05,454 --> 00:18:07,054
<i>my best friends.</i>

362
00:18:07,088 --> 00:18:10,188
<i>The only family</i>
<i>I've ever known.</i>

363
00:18:10,221 --> 00:18:12,121
Ta-daa!

364
00:18:16,121 --> 00:18:18,354
[CROWD CHEERING, CLAPPING]

365
00:18:20,121 --> 00:18:21,354
All right!

366
00:18:27,621 --> 00:18:28,788
Ringmaster.

367
00:18:29,888 --> 00:18:30,921
Stay back.

368
00:18:30,954 --> 00:18:32,921
Huh?

369
00:18:32,954 --> 00:18:35,554
Reno, you have
a gift.

370
00:18:35,588 --> 00:18:36,954
Use it.

371
00:18:36,988 --> 00:18:38,421
You're no longer
Reno the robot.

372
00:18:38,454 --> 00:18:40,888
It's time to start
being human.

373
00:18:40,921 --> 00:18:43,021
B-but I can't just leave you.

374
00:18:43,054 --> 00:18:44,421
You must.

375
00:18:44,454 --> 00:18:46,554
Go, and become a human
we can be proud of.

376
00:18:46,588 --> 00:18:49,254
[CRYING]

377
00:18:49,288 --> 00:18:50,821
[GROWLS]

378
00:18:50,854 --> 00:18:52,421
Yeah, yeah.
Break out the violins.

379
00:18:52,454 --> 00:18:53,821
Arrest them now!

380
00:18:53,854 --> 00:18:55,154
CRAVEN:
No!

381
00:18:56,621 --> 00:18:59,954
Everyone...these robots
never kidnapped anybody.

382
00:18:59,988 --> 00:19:01,554
Gustav just made it up.

383
00:19:01,588 --> 00:19:02,954
[GROWLS]

384
00:19:02,988 --> 00:19:04,321
Craven!

385
00:19:05,554 --> 00:19:07,354
Careful.

386
00:19:07,388 --> 00:19:09,821
I've had enough
of your bullying!

387
00:19:09,854 --> 00:19:11,188
I'm the mayor,

388
00:19:11,221 --> 00:19:14,221
and I hereby clear
these robots of any crime.

389
00:19:14,254 --> 00:19:18,854
And I invite them to be the
official circus of Bella Notte.

390
00:19:18,888 --> 00:19:19,988
ALL:
Huh?

391
00:19:21,154 --> 00:19:22,788
[CHEERING]

392
00:19:24,154 --> 00:19:25,888
[GROWLING]

393
00:19:34,054 --> 00:19:35,288
ASTRO:
Reno.

394
00:19:39,988 --> 00:19:41,088
Dr. O'Shay,

395
00:19:41,121 --> 00:19:43,054
I'm ready to go
to the city now.

396
00:19:43,088 --> 00:19:44,521
Let's go.

397
00:19:44,554 --> 00:19:45,888
Mm-hm.

398
00:19:48,388 --> 00:19:49,821
ASTRO:
You sure you won't
get homesick

399
00:19:49,854 --> 00:19:52,188
for the
robot circus, Reno?

400
00:19:52,221 --> 00:19:54,054
Oh, maybe.
But no matter

401
00:19:54,088 --> 00:19:56,288
how far apart we are,
we're still a family.

402
00:19:56,321 --> 00:19:57,521
And when I'm
a robotics engineer,

403
00:19:57,554 --> 00:19:59,154
I just come back
and help 'em.

404
00:19:59,188 --> 00:20:00,321
Cool.

405
00:20:05,588 --> 00:20:07,254
Well, the mayor really

406
00:20:07,288 --> 00:20:09,354
spared no expense
for our grand reopening.

407
00:20:09,388 --> 00:20:11,288
I wonder if Reno can see

408
00:20:11,321 --> 00:20:13,588
the fireworks
from where he is.

409
00:20:13,621 --> 00:20:15,154
I can barely see 'em.

410
00:20:15,188 --> 00:20:18,288
Whose idea was it
to shoot 'em off in the daytime?

411
00:20:18,321 --> 00:20:20,854
Come on, guys.
It's showtime.

412
00:20:20,888 --> 00:20:21,988
All right!
Let's get going.

413
00:20:22,021 --> 00:20:23,321
Yahoo!

414
00:20:23,354 --> 00:20:25,321
Looks like
the show's starting.

415
00:20:25,354 --> 00:20:28,388
Yeah. And so is...

416
00:20:28,421 --> 00:20:29,888
my new life.

417
00:20:37,954 --> 00:20:40,321
[♪]

